{
  "stem": "15694.11",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 15.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 54,
      "text": "And the SS, you know, they closed us-- the-- the shutters in.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 55,
      "text": "And they were hiding, either under the train or ran into the nearby woods.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 56,
      "text": "It was also something I missed in Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 57,
      "text": "There was an alarm.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 58,
      "text": "And the only bomb fell not too far away from me, belying the-- the Allied-- the Allieds saying that Auschwitz couldn't be bombed.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 59,
      "text": "It was too far.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 60,
      "text": "But one bomb-- bomb-- bomb dropped there, you know, on the way to Germany.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 61,
      "text": "Come back to this.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 62,
      "text": "And it was, you know, a joy to see the SS running for their lives, the masters.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 63,
      "text": "And I only hoped that the bomb wouldn't kill me.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 64,
      "text": "Sort of-- that would be sort of ironical.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 65,
      "text": "And I'm sure that it might have happened some other places where they were killed by friendly bombs, friendly fire, so to say.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 66,
      "text": "Anyway, a nearby train was bombed.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 67,
      "text": "And people were let out too rummage-- except for the Jews-- rummage in that train, for anything they could use.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 68,
      "text": "Preferably something to eat.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 69,
      "text": "And I'm not sure if it was mockery that the next train, the Jews were allowed to go out.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 70,
      "text": "And we went to the train.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 71,
      "text": "And we looked and we looked.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 72,
      "text": "And I had a wagon to myself.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 73,
      "text": "There weren't many Jews.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But what could I find?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I found an onion.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I don't know if it's got any sulfur.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I was afraid it might even hurt-- harm me.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I had, in the train, somebody from the-- from the day when people sort of went and got them self food, some raw potato came to me.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I ate it, bit by bit, the raw-- in the raw way.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Anyway, this day I found that onion.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I was wondering if I could eat it.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
